{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μάρτῠς</b>, ὁ, ἡ, <br /> Cretan dialect, Epid. <b>μαῖτυς</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Leg.Gort.” 1.13, +others, “IG” 42(1).42\">Refs</a>], Cretan dialect also <b>μαίτυρς</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 4998\">Refs</a>] see ii; <i>genitive</i> μάρτῠρος, <i>accusative</i> -ῠρα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 371, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], formed from <b>μάρτυρ</b> (which see), except <i>accusative</i> μάρτῠν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 84. 4, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 1034, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.49a\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <i>dative</i> <i>plural</i> μάρτῠσι (but μάρτυρσι probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Hipponax Iambographus 51)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>witness</b> (not in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus), 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus [same place], “hymnus ad Mercurium” 372, 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1226, etc.; ἄμμιν μάρτυς ἔστω Ζεύς 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.167, compare 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 664; ἁμέραι δ᾽ ἐπίλοιποι μ. σοφώτατοι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 1.34; τούτων μάρτυρας καλῶ θεούς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1248, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 491; μάρτυρα θέσθαι τινά [prev. author] “Supp.” 261; μ. θεοὺς ποιεῖσθαι 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.87, etc.; μάρτυρι χρῆσθαί τινι 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1375b30 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μάρτυρας παρέχεσθαι produce <b>witnesses</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 471e, compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 27.51, etc.; μάρτυρες παρίστανται 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.6.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μάρτυρα παράγεσθαι, μάρτυρας ἐπάγεσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\"